> We're always up for a sweet and savory dinner pairing, and these tacos are just
> that. Chicken breast strips are cooked in a sweet soy glaze until the glaze is
> sticky and the chicken is tender. They're stuffed into steamy tortillas,
> along with a tangy, cilantro-flecked cabbage slaw. Of course, we'd never skip
> out on taco toppings, and these ones don't disappoint: There's creamy, spicy
> sriracha mayo and crispy fried onions. It's all ready in just 15 minutes—life
> is sweet (and savory), friends.

Wash and dry all produce. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Halve, core, and
thinly slice @long green pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced).

In a #medium bowl{}, toss together @coleslaw mix{4%ounce}, half the
@rice wine vinegar{2.5%teaspoon}, half the cilantro, @sugar{0.5%teaspoon}, and
a pinch of @salt{} until thoroughly combined.

== Chicken Stir-Fry ==

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all
over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add green pepper and cook until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add chicken and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through,
~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon} and cook until everything is coated and
glaze has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from heat.

== Sriracha Mayo ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} with
@sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and
pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

== Assembly ==

Divide tortillas between #plates{} and fill with chicken mixture and slaw
(draining first). Top with sriracha mayo, @crispy fried onions{1}, and
remaining cilantro. Serve.